Most of us are so used to electric kettles by now that we might even have forgotten how a standard whistling kettle works. Here's the Musical Kettle concept by Naoki Kawamoto that is interesting to look at and listen to, although it won't be too practical in a cramped kitchen where space is at a premium. This kettle can spew out sounds according to your favorite tune when the water has reached its boiling point, hence the rather long snout.